<class module="niagaraDriver" runtimeProfile="rt" qualifiedName="com.tridium.nd.BNSpaceScheme" name="BNSpaceScheme" packageName="com.tridium.nd" public="true">
<description>
&lt;p&gt;BNSpaceScheme &#x22;nspace:&#x22; to a BComponentSpace or BVirtualComponentSpace.&lt;/p&gt;&#xa;&#xa; &lt;p&gt;Introduced in Niagara 4.4, this scheme allows for an optional&#xa; body String that indicates a target station name. At resolution time, if this station name body&#xa; is empty, it will just return the default station space for the current session.&#xa; If the station name body is present, it will first check to see if the station name matches&#xa; that of the default station space for the current session and return it if so.&#xa; If the station name body is present and doesn&#x27;t match the default station space for the&#xa; current session, next it will attempt to lookup a matching NiagaraStation (by name) in the&#xa; NiagaraNetwork and return its virtual component space (if available). If a match is&#xa; still not found, lastly it will check to see if the station name body matches a&#xa; reachable station (see &lt;code&gt;<see ref="com.tridium.nd.sysdef.BReachableStations">BReachableStations</see>&lt;/code&gt; and&#xa; &lt;code&gt;<see ref="com.tridium.nd.sysdef.BReachableStationInfo">BReachableStationInfo</see>&lt;/code&gt;), and if so, it resolves to the root virtual&#xa; component of that reachable station from the perspective of the local one. If&#xa; a station name is present in the body and doesn&#x27;t match any of the above&#xa; criteria, an UnresolvedException occurs at resolution time.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
<tag name="@author">Scott Hoye</tag>
<tag name="@creation">14 Feb 17</tag>
<tag name="@since">Niagara 4.4</tag>
<extends>
<type class="javax.baja.space.BSpaceScheme"/>
</extends>
